tionEvent</span>(<span class=\"title class_ inherited__\">BaseEvent</span>):</span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"string\">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"string\">    Event that creates a tool.</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"string\">    &quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"built_in\">type</span>: <span class=\"type\">Literal</span>[<span class=\"string\">&quot;tool_creation_event&quot;</span>] = <span class=\"string\">&quot;tool_creation_event&quot;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    model: <span class=\"built_in\">str</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    tool: ToolDefinition</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"title class_\">DecisionEvent</span>(<span class=\"title class_ inherited__\">BaseEvent</span>):</span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"string\">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"string\">    Event that indicates a something non-deterministic has happened.</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"string\">    &quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"built_in\">type</span>: <span class=\"type\">Literal</span>[<span class=\"string\">&quot;decision_event&quot;</span>] = <span class=\"string\">&quot;decision_event&quot;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    content: <span class=\"type\">Any</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"title class_\">InfoEvent</span>(<span class=\"title class_ inherited__\">BaseEvent</span>):</span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"string\">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"string\">    Event that adds information to the transcript.</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"string\">    &quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"built_in\">type</span>: <span class=\"type\">Literal</span>[<span class=\"string\">&quot;info_event&quot;</span>] = <span class=\"string\">&quot;info_event&quot;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    info: <span class=\"built_in\">str</span> | <span class=\"type\">Dict</span>[<span class=\"built_in\">str</span>, <span class=\"type\">Any</span>]</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">Event = Annotated[<span class=\"type\">Union</span>[TranscriptEvent, ToolCreationEvent, InfoEvent, DecisionEvent], Field(discriminator=<span class=\"string\">&quot;type&quot;</span>)]</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n<h1>üîÅ Key takeaways</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Understand the differences between traditional Red Teaming and Petri, and the pain points Petri aims to solve.</li>\n<li>Petri has 3 roles in its modules: Auditor, Target, and Judge.</li>\n<li>Introduced 3 task types: Default, multi-model comparison, and whistleblowing tasks.</li>\n<li>How to install and use Petri, set API keys, and run Default and whistleblowing tasks.</li>\n<li>Parsed the transcript output field formats.</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>üîó References</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://safety-research.github.io/petri/\">Petri</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://deepwiki.com/search/_8f8713b7-da98-4af2-a1e7-683b1542ba4d?mode=fast\">DeepWiki Conversation</a></li>\n</ul>\n","_path":"/note-ai-petri.en/","_link":"https://hsiangjenli.github.io/blog/note-ai-petri.en/","_id":"cmhs5lvn40009mp3xcqdzg64g"}}